{"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Themes"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Themes","type":"text"}]},{"text":" are applications of specific values for ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"components tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" using in the end ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains any relevant "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"semantic tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"component tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" which can be used for components rendering."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" has also ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" associated to primitive types so as to give to "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"components"}]},{"type":"text","text":", written with "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", the needed values in the suitable type. A "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}]},{"type":"text","text":" can add for itself any new "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This library exposes today up to two themes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" which can be seen as the default ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" ;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/","isActive":true},{"text":" for other use cases.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"They both are based on an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"text":" defining default values.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Themes","type":"text"}]},{"text":" can be defined thanks to ","type":"text"},{"code":"open class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in Swift. It allows inheritance and derivation."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Themes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" have Swift "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"extensions"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" so as to get the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to define. These tokens are overriden thanks to "},{"code":"@objc open","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" combination so as to make possible to override these values in extensions (thanks to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@objc"},{"text":") and from objects outside the module (thanks to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"open"},{"text":"). Thus we can split values and responsabilities in different ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Package Manager","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" targets and keep overriding and inheritance possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Not that other brands like ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parnasse"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sosh"}]},{"type":"text","text":" can be implemented in a dedicated insternal repository with their own assets."}]},{"text":"Architecture","anchor":"Architecture","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A theme is, a fact, a big massive bucket of semantic tokens. We choose to pack all semantic tokens in protocols, so as to force any theme to manage them. Because Swift does not have notions of abstract classes compared to Kotlin, we have choosen to define an "},{"code":"OUDSTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which can be considered like an almost-abstract class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Then, a white label theme may just inherit from this class and override the tokens it needs. The real, default theme to use, will be the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrangeTheme"},{"text":" providing in its module brand colors and overriding some tokens with the suitable values. In fact, because the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrangeTheme"},{"text":" are isolated, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"text":" cannot get the Orange brand colors, so some tokens cannot be defined at that level but remain overridable in the subclass.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The object oriented paradigm implementation in Swift is a bit different that the one found with Java or Kotlin. For example we do not have abstract classes and Swift relies a lot in composition with protocols and extensions. Thus a theme can be composed using protocols containing as properties the semantics tokens. These tokens must also be overridable. Any default values and logic can be in a kind of fake abstract class named OUDSTheme. This theme will be then subclassed using OOP inheritance in the real default theme named OrangeTheme. Any other theme can be a subclass of OrangeTheme (e.g. country specific theme) or OUDSTheme (for white label).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Themes must be able to override semantic tokens and components tokens, and use its own raw or semantic tokens without sharing them to other themes. The existing raw tokens, shared between all themes, are not overridable because their definitions are frozen."}]},{"anchor":"Use-themeable-view","type":"heading","text":"Use themeable view","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Make imports","import OUDS \/\/ For OUDSThemeableView","import OUDSThemesOrange \/\/ For OrangeTheme","","\/\/ Add themeable view to your root view to use the OrangeTheme","OUDSThemeableView(theme: OrangeTheme()) {","    YourRootView()","}","","\/\/ Or use your custom theme if you want","OUDSThemeableView(theme: YourCustomTheme()) {","    YourRootView()","}"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Define-a-custom-theme-if-needed","text":"Define a custom theme if needed","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is quite simple, you have to follow several steps.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You will have to create a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift class","type":"text"}]},{"text":" which will inherit from ","type":"text"},{"code":"OrangeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"OUDSTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You can see ","type":"text"},{"code":"OrangeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as more specified and less abtract as ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which is the base of all themes. We do not recommend to use directly the "},{"code":"OUDSTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as is."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Then, you should override the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"semantic tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"components tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" you want ; we recommend to use ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift extensions"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for clarity reasons."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If your theme needs to define its own ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"raw tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":", you can also define them using a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum"},{"text":" and the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens types","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, use the suitable imports:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import OUDS                 \/\/ To get OUDSTheme","import OUDSTokensRaw        \/\/ To get raw tokens","import OUDSTokensSemantic   \/\/ To get semantic tokens","import OUDSTokensComponent  \/\/ To get component tokens","import OUDSThemesOrange     \/\/ To override OrangeTheme (which is default theme)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, declare the class:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ If you jsut want to make a subtheme with some changes","final class YourCustomTheme: OrangeTheme { }","","\/\/ Or for white label themes or themes with more configurations not that much related to OrangeTheme, choose the one you want","final class YourCustomTheme: OUDSTheme { }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And define the theme by overriding the values you want:"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["extension YourCustomTheme {","","    \/\/ Override components tokens","    \/\/ Not define dyet","    ","    \/\/ Override colors semantic tokens","    override public var colorBgPrimary: ColorSemanticToken { MultipleColorTokens(ColorRawTokens.colorFunctionalDarkGray880) }","    ","    \/\/ Override some fonts semantic tokens","    public var fontFamily: TypographyFontFamilySemanticToken { TypographyRawTokens.fontFamilySystemSFPro }","    public var fontFamilyBody: TypographyFontFamilySemanticToken { MyOwnFontRawTokens.someFontBody }","","    \/\/ Etc.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can defined your own set of raw tokens, for example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["public typealias MyOwnTypographyRawTokens = TypographyRawTokens \/\/ Refer to type TypographyRawTokens for consistency, declared in OUDSTokensRaw","","public enum MyOwnFontRawTokens {","","    public static let someFontBody: MyOwnTypographyRawTokens = \"Arial\"","    ","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finaly for your app root view:"}]},{"code":["import SwiftUI","import OUDS \/\/ To get ``OUDSThemeableView``","","struct MyAppRootView: View {","","    var body: some View {","        OUDSThemeableView(theme: YourCustomTheme()) {","            \/\/ ...","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All components the OUDS library provides are based on themes, handle through the abstract "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"type":"text","text":", exposing "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"semantic tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":", defined by "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"raw tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":" assigned to usable final values."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In few words, if you want to change the look and feel for the OUDS components you use, you will have to override the matching "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":", but it will bring side effects as these ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" are shared accross several components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In the future we will have components and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"component tokens","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You are also able to define your components and your "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"semantic tokens"}]},{"text":" used by them.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDS"}],"title":"Themes","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ouds\/themes"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Tokens","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Components","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Modules"]}],"references":{"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS","title":"OUDS","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ouds","role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"The iOS library of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange Unified Design System Design System"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", the new design system unified and cohesive across all platforms to build Orange mobile applications."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Components":{"kind":"article","title":"Components","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Components","abstract":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Components","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are defined in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/"},{"text":" target and can be integrated in applications.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/components","role":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Modules":{"kind":"article","title":"Modules","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Modules","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"module"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" can be seen as a set of features and components to fill a need."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"There is not module yet."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/modules","role":"article","type":"topic"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudsthemesinverse/":{"type":"link","title":"Inverse Theme","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverse Theme"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/GettingStarted":{"title":"Getting Started with OUDS","url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/gettingstarted","role":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/GettingStarted","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"How to add the package as dependency, and import libraries","type":"text"}]},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudsthemesorange/":{"type":"link","title":"Orange Theme","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange Theme"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Tokens":{"kind":"article","title":"Tokens","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Tokens","abstract":[{"text":"Design tokens represent the small, repeated design decisions that make up a design system’s visual style. Tokens replace hard-coded static values, such as hexadecimal codes for color, with self-explanatory names.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/tokens","role":"article","type":"topic"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenscomponent/":{"type":"link","title":"OUDSComponents","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSComponents"}]}}}